qt-commander (0.1.10-1) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

* The initial directories which are shown can now be set via the command-line.
  For example, `qt-commander /tmp` will show the directory `/tmp` on the left
  side (and the home directory on the right side). When two directory paths
  are given, the first one is opened on the left side and the second one on the
  right side.

* The text viewer can now provide basic syntax highlighting for the Java and
  Pascal programming languages and the SQL database query language, too.

* When the view button is clicked while a directory is selected, it will now
  trigger a change to that directory instead of showing a warning that only
  files can be viewed.

* The speed of the text viewer's syntax highlighting has been improved for the
  existing programming languages from earlier versions.

 -- Dirk Stolle <striezel-dev@web.de>  Fri, 19 Jun 2026 03:42:37 +0200

qt-commander (0.1.9-1) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  * A new configuration option allows to change the delete operation for files /
    directories from actual deletion to move to trash.

  * All settings can now be edited in a new dialog. This dialog also includes
    the settings used by the various file viewers.

 -- Dirk Stolle <striezel-dev@web.de>  Sun, 31 May 2026 23:31:27 +0200

